# Lumiverb — Architecture Rules

## Source of Truth
- System design: @docs/architecture.md
- API rules: @docs/cursor-api.md
- CLI rules: @docs/cursor-cli.md
- If a request conflicts with any of these documents, **stop and notify before acting**.
- If a planned change contradicts any doc under `docs/`, notify me to confirm whether
  the spec should be updated or the plan is out of spec.

## Multi-Tenancy — Non-Negotiable
- Every tenant has their own isolated PostgreSQL database. No shared tables between tenants.
- The control plane DB (tenants, api_keys, routing) is entirely separate from tenant DBs.
- Tenant context always comes from the API key — never from a URL parameter or request body.
- Use the tenant DB routing layer to resolve connections. Never hardcode a connection string.

## API Design
- All routes under `/v1/`.
- Authentication: `Authorization: Bearer <api_key>` header only.
- Cursor pagination everywhere — never offset pagination.
- Error envelope: `{"error": {"code": "...", "message": "...", "details": {...}}}`
- File uploads via multipart. Files served via signed URLs — never raw object storage URLs.

## Phase 1 Scope — Do Not Build
- No user authentication or session management (Phase 5)
- No webhooks
- Do not populate or query `embedding_vector`, `faces`, `people`, or `face_person_matches`
  (Phase 2 — columns exist, are nullable, must stay untouched in Phase 1)
- No cross-tenant or multi-library search
- No rate limiting

## Documentation
- When adding API endpoints, CLI commands, or schema changes, update the relevant file under `docs/`.
- Check for an existing guide before creating a new one.
